                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/biol-304" class="program-course-title">
              BIOL 304 Evolution (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-18774" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Biology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Biology (Sci)              : This course will show how the theory of evolution by natural selection provides the basis for understanding the whole of biology. The first half of the course describes the process of selection, while the second deals with evolution in the long term.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Graham Bell (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>3 hours lecture</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: BIOL 205 and BIOL 215 or ENVR 202</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
