                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/biol-310" class="program-course-title">
              BIOL 310 Biodiversity and Ecosystems (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-18786" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Biology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Biology (Sci)              : Ecological bases of the natural causes and consequences of current global environmental changes, including how biodiversity and ecosystem processes are defined and measured, how they vary in space and time, how they are affected by physical and biological factors, and how they affect each other and human societies.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Thomas Davies (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Winter</li>
              <li>3 hours lecture</li>
              <li>one-day field trip to Mont St-Hilaire</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: BIOL 215; or ENVR 200 and ENVR 202; MATH 112 or equivalent; or permission of the instructor</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
